#' This function takes as an input a pxn matrix in which each column is a sampling unit
#' and each row is one marker and outputs the n-by-n linear kernel matrix
#' @param X is a pxn matrix in which each column is a sampling unit and each row is one marker
#' @details We obtain a linear kernel
#' @export linear.kernel
#' @author Arnab Maity

linear.kernel = function(X){	return(t(X)%*%X)  }
